name: Reverse Grinch
title: Nike Kobe 6 Protro Reverse Grinch
description:
Step into the future while honoring a legend with the Nike Kobe 6 Protro Reverse Grinch. This long-awaited sneaker, flips the script on the iconic Grinch colorway. Boasting a Bright Crimson upper that mirrors the intensity of Kobe's game, this shoe is a standout piece in any collection. The snakeskin-textured upper, a nod to the Black Mamba himself, is complemented by black Swooshes and electrifying Electric Green accents.

The Reverse Grinch doesn't just turn heads with its colorway; it pays homage to Kobe Bryant's enduring legacy. Electric Green laces and Kobe branding on the tongues and heels add to its unique charm. The midsole and heel counter, wrapped in Bright Crimson, maintain the shoe’s bold and cohesive look, ensuring it stands out on the court and in the streets.

Set to release on December 16, 2023, for $190, the Nike Kobe 6 Protro Reverse Grinch is more than a sneaker—it's a tribute to a basketball icon. With its vivid colors and sleek design, it's a must-have for sneakerheads and basketball fans alike.

name: The Powerpuff Girls Bubbles
title: Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Bubbles
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Bubbles edition brings a playful and vibrant twist to the iconic Dunk Low silhouette. Inspired by the cartoon show, this Dunk Low is a perfect representation of sugar, spice, and everything nice, channeling the charm and energy of Bubbles.

Featuring the colorway Blue Chill/Deep Royal Blue/Active Pink, this sneaker is a visual treat, capturing the essence of Bubbles' character. Each design element is thoughtfully crafted to reflect the cheerful and spirited nature of one of the beloved Powerpuff Girls.

Released on December 14 at skate shops and on December 15 on SNKRS, the Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Bubbles was priced at $135. This sneaker is a must-have for fans of the series and sneaker collectors alike, offering a unique blend of nostalgia and style.

name: The Powerpuff Girls Buttercup
title: Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Buttercup
description:
Embrace the bold and daring with the Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Buttercup. This edition captures Buttercup's fearless and tough personality, reflected in the Mean Green/Black/Lotus Pink colorway. The design elements of the sneaker are as dynamic and powerful as Buttercup herself, making a strong statement.

The sneaker's striking color palette is complemented by its high-quality construction and attention to detail, embodying the spirit of the fierce Powerpuff Girl. This Dunk Low is not just a shoe; it's an expression of Buttercup's unyielding energy and charisma.

Released on December 14 at skate shops and on SNKRS, and priced at $135, the Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Buttercup is a perfect mix of style and attitude. Sneaker enthusiasts and fans of the show will not want to miss this unique and spirited sneaker.​

name: The Powerpuff Girls Blossom
title: Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Blossom
description:
Step into style and sophistication with the Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Blossom. Representing Blossom's intelligent and graceful character, this sneaker is adorned in a Lotus Pink/Digital Pink/Medium Soft Pink colorway. The design is a fitting tribute to the leader of the Powerpuff Girls, combining elegance with a touch of playfulness. The Blossom edition of the Dunk Low is a harmonious blend of soft hues and quality materials, encapsulating Blossom's charm and poise.

Released on December 14 at skate shops and on SNKRS for $135, the Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Blossom is an enchanting addition to any sneaker collection. It's a celebration of the hit cartoon and beautiful design, making it a highly desirable piece for fans and sneakerheads​.

name: KAWS Sky High Farm Workwear White
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low KAWS Sky High Farm Workwear White
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low KAWS Sky High Farm Workwear in White is a unique blend of classic style and artistic flair. Featuring the timeless 1982 model's design, these sneakers stay true to Sky High Farm’s commitment to sustainability while adding a contemporary twist. The most striking feature is the iconic Nike Swooshes, transformed into puffy grey cloud-like figures through printed, dye-cut appliques layered over the original logos. The subtlety of KAWS' distinctive art style breathes uniqueness into these Air Force 1s, making them immediately distinguishable.

The extraordinary Nike Air Force 1 Low KAWS Sky High Farm Workwear in White released on December 16th. These sneakers launched in limited quantities, making them a coveted item in the sneaker world.

name: x NOCTA Women's Chalet Polar
title: Nike x NOCTA Women's Chalet Polar Top Dark Blue

name: Photon Dust (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Photon Dust (Women's)
description:
The women's Nike Dunk Low Photon Dust (W) is made of white leather with Photon Dust leather overlays and Swooshes. A woven Nike label on the tongue and embroidered Nike branding completes the design.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Photon Dust (W) released in May of 2021 and retailed for $100.

name: White Black Panda
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black Panda
description:
From the school-spirited College Colors Program to the vibrant Nike CO.JP collection, Nike Dunks have seen many colorways since the design’s inception in 1985. But with each new colorway, the Dunk’s classic color-blocking has remained in some capacity. Nike put its timeless color-blocking to work with the Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black.

The upper Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black is constructed of white leather with black leather overlays and Swooshes. Classic Nike branding is featured on the nylon tongue, nodding to traditional Dunk design elements. A white midsole and black outsole complete the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black released in January of 2021 and retailed for $100.

To shop all Nike Dunks, click here.

name: Grey Fog
title: Nike Dunk Low Grey Fog
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Grey Fog features a white leather upper with Grey Fog leather overlays and Swooshes. From there, a matching woven tongue label, heel tab, and sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Grey Fog released in September of 2021 and retailed for $100.

name: Cacao Wow (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Cacao Wow (Women's)
description:
Nike did it again on July 28, 2023, when they dropped the Dunk Low in the enticing Cacao Wow colorway. This shoe is a surefire hit for those who crave unique kicks.

Crafted with buttery smooth leather, the upper sports a cool Cacao Wow finish, delivering a potent mix of style and comfort. This Dunk Low uses a light, creamy hue for contrast, adding just the right amount of pop.The Cacao Wow Dunk Low is set to turn heads and start conversations

This Nike Dunk in the Cacao Wow colorway was released on July 28, 2023, coming in at a retail price of $110.

name: Reverse Grinch (GS)
title: Nike Kobe 6 Protro Reverse Grinch (GS)

name: Polar Blue
title: Nike Dunk Low Polar Blue
description:
The Nike Dunk Low in Polar Blue is a unique and crisp colorway of the Dunk Low shoes traditionally worn on the basketball court since the mid-1980s. This shoe has seen technological updates since its debut, resulting in this comfortable and visually striking iteration, and has also become an iconic streetwear shoe.

This iteration of the Nike Dunk Low is constructed with leather uppers and a rubber outsole. The base is white rubber, and Polar Blue overlays line the perforated toebox, the heel, the laces, and the midsole. The Nike Swoosh also appears in Polar Blue on the midsole. The tongue is padded for comfort, and white Nike branding is also visible on the heel.

Our StockX experts believe the standout feature of this sneaker is the Polar Blue overlays on the white leather base. The color makes the shoe appear crisp and clean, allowing for both sports wear and casual wear. The Nike Dunk Low in Polar Blue was released on October 14th, 2023, at a retail price of $115.

name: White Black Panda (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black Panda (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low White Black 2021 women’s sneaker features a white and black leather upper with perforations on the toe box. The base of the upper starts with white leather, and black leather wraps around it in an even pattern. A black Nike Swoosh logo adorns either side of the upper and wraps around the ankle to complete the design.

The Nike Dunk Low White Black 2021 women’s sneaker released in March of 2021 and retailed for $100.

To shop all Nike Dunks, click here.

name: White
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 White
description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low White ‘07 features an all-white leather upper with a perforated toe box and Swoosh overlays. A Nike heel embroidery and white sole completes the design.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low White ‘07 originally released in 2007, but since it is an essential colorway to the brand, it consistently restocks.

To shop all Nike Air Force 1 shoes, click here.

name: St. John's (2020/2023)
title: Nike Dunk Low SP St. John's (2020/2023)
description:
Nike celebrated the 35th Anniversary of the Nike Dunk by releasing the Nike Dunk Low SP St. John's (2020), now available on StockX. The Nike Dunk debuted as part of the 1985 Nike College Color’s program, a program that delivered footwear in the school colors of 12 popular basketball programs allowing fans to support their favorite teams from head to toe. This St. John's colorway was among the first collegiate colorways Nike released, breaking the mold for colorways used on basketball shoes.

The Nike Dunk Low SP St. John's is composed of a white leather upper with red leather overlays. A white midsole, red outsole, and classic Nike branding on the tongue completes the design. These sneakers released in June of 2020 and retailed for $100 and again in October of 2023 and retailed for $110.

name: White Black Panda (GS)
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black Panda (GS)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (GS) silhouette comes in a stark black and white colorway and is made from premium leather materials throughout. Additionally, white Nike lettering complements the rear ankle support of the silhouette while the Nike Air text along with the customary company Swoosh logo adorns the tongue. In keeping with the color scheme, a white midsole resting atop a black outsole rounds out the look of this Dunk Low Retro shoe.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (GS) released in March of 2021 and retailed for $85.

name: Triple Pink (GS)
title: Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (GS)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink has a full leather build, which makes use of three distinct shades of pink to complete the look. The base has a light shade of pink, with a slightly contrasting pink overlay.

The look is completed by the Nike Swoosh in a bold pink that provides a strong contrast and stands out noticeably on the shoe. In addition to the Swoosh on both sides, the Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Grade School) features Nike branding on the sole, heel, tongue, and inner sole. This shoe comes in Grade School (GS) sizing.

The Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Grade School) was released in early June, 2022, at the retail price of $85.

name: TIGHTBOOTH
title: Nike SB Dunk Low TIGHTBOOTH
description:
The TIGHTBOOTH x Nike SB Dunk Low is where the heartbeat of the city meets the soul of skate culture. Releasing on November 14, 2023, this sneaker is a celebration of the skateboarding scene and the urban landscape it thrives in. The White/Black-Safety Orange colorway mirrors the street lights and city nights, serving as a beacon for skaters everywhere.

This collaboration is about more than just looks—it's about the feel of the board underfoot and the grip on the pavement. The reflective elements and textural contrasts are inspired by the very streets that skaters call home. It’s a sneaker that doesn't just stand out visually; it's built to perform under the cover of darkness, embodying the essence of nocturnal sessions.

At $135, the TIGHTBOOTH Nike SB Sunk Low collaboration is an investment into the legacy of street skating. It's a bold statement piece for those who make the city their playground after sundown.

name: Born X Raised One Block At A Time
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Born X Raised One Block At A Time
description:
Introducing the Born x Raised One Block At A Time Nike SB Dunk Low, showcased in a Deep Royal Blue and White colorway.

This isn't just another Dunk – it's a collaboration with the legendary LA brand, Born x Raised. Representing the culture of LA with a hint of luxury, the upper mixes premium leather with nubuck and silver detailing on the iconic Nike Swoosh & heel tab. "One Block At a Time" is embroidered on the mudguard & featured on the tongue. The heel features "On The Turf" with an extra Nike Swoosh on the back of the midsole. Ensuring you're not only wearing a shoe but a statement. This shoe effortlessly mirrors LA's vibrant and dynamic style. Its design boasts of its heritage while nudging to the future. And of course, the iconic Dunk silhouette ensures a snug fit and ultimate comfort.

In essence, the Born x Raised collab is where street meets sneaker. This masterpiece dropped on shelves at a retail price of $130.

name: April Skateboards
title: Nike SB Dunk Low April Skateboards
description:
Strap in for a ride with the Nike SB Dunk Low April Skateboards, a sneaker that’s as much about performance as it is about making a statement. The Turbo Green/Metallic Silver/Turbo Green colorway is a nod to the fearless energy of the skate parks.

The design stays true to the SB Dunk Low's heritage, blending functionality with street-ready aesthetics. This sneaker brings a bold twist to the classic design, incorporating a color pop that stands out against the concrete playgrounds. It's built to withstand the scrapes and scratches of skate life, all while keeping your style on point.

Priced at a cool $120, the April Skateboards edition is an affordable piece of skateboarding's rich culture. Set to drop on November 27, 2023. It's a colorway that represents more than just style. It's a testament to the skate scene's vibrant personality and a must-have for those who live to ride.

name: Aunt Pearl
title: Nike KD 16 Aunt Pearl
description:
The Nike KD 16 NRG Aunt Pearl continues the tradition of paying tribute to Kevin Durant’s Aunt Pearl, who offered support in his formative years and lost her battle with lung cancer in 2000.

This sneaker stands out from other "Aunt Pearl" variations due to the floral-debossed overlay which covers the mesh upper and features a paisley pattern. Durable TPU support wings connect to the midsole and boast rose-like blooms beneath a transparent seal. The Phylon midsole comes with a Zoom Air unit in the forefoot and a responsive Air Strobel unit beneath the heel. The sneaker features a primarily pink colorway of White, Fierce Pink, Pink Foam, and Hyper Pink.

Something our StockX experts love is the addition of fuzzy laces. These light-hued laces complement the textile-like mesh of the upper and the woven material that makes up the tongue. The Nike KD 16 NRG Aunt Pearl was released on October 27, 2023, and retailed at $170.

name: Supreme White
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Supreme White
description:
Supreme and Nike paid homage to an NYC classic with the release of the Nike Air Force 1 Low Supreme White, now available on StockX. This collaboration adds Supreme’s world-renowned Box Logo to the side of a traditional all-white Air Force 1 design.

This Air Force 1 Low is comprised of an all-white leather upper with matching soles and detailing. A red Supreme Box Logo placed on the outside heel completes the design. These sneakers released in March of 2020 and retailed for $118.

name: Smoke Grey Gum 3M Swoosh
title: Nike Dunk Low Smoke Grey Gum 3M Swoosh
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Smoke Grey Gum 3M Swoosh draws inspiration from the Nike Skateboarding Orange Label collection. However, the grey tone colorway and use of premium materials upgrade the classic low-top silhouette synonymous with Nike SB sneakers.

The grey suede and tumbled leather overlays balance out the clean, white upper and the light brown of the gum sole. The heel tabs, which feature ‘NIKE’ in white stitching, and the soft, cloth liner add additional accents in Light Iron Ore and Smoke Grey. Featuring laces with a reflective, speckled pattern, the lace cage houses a mesh tongue displaying Nike branding.

Something we love about this shoe is the 3M reflective detailing on the grey panel Swoosh. It increases visibility during low lighting and exemplifies the attention to detail found in this Nike Dunk Low variation. The Nike Dunk Low Smoke Grey Gum 3M Swoosh was released on October 3, 2023, and retailed at $115.

name: Rose Whisper (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Rose Whisper (Women's)
description:
The women's Nike Dunk Low Rose Whisper arrives in a classic two-tone color blocked look similar to the original Nike Dunks of the 1980s. This Dunk offers a warm palette primed for the summer weather, with a white and Rose Whisper leather construction. Matching woven tongue labels contribute to the design's retro feel, while an EVA foam sole provides cushioning.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Rose Whisper released in June of 2022 and retailed for $100.

name: Medium Curry
title: Nike Dunk Low Medium Curry
description:
Nike added a luxe twist to the Dunk Low with the Nike Dunk Low Medium Curry. The Curry colorway first made its way onto the Nike Dunk Low in 1999 as part of the Nike CO.JP (Concept Japan) collection. Since then, there have been multiple Curry Dunk releases in Nike’s catalog, including the 2003 Nike Dunk High Premium Curry, 2010 Nike Dunk Low VNTG Dark Curry, and now, the Nike Dunk Low Medium Curry.

The upper of the Nike Dunk Low Medium Curry is composed of Sail hairy suede with Medium Curry overlays and a Bone-colored Swoosh. Nike branding is present on its traditional woven tongue tag and Medium Curry heel patch. A Sail nylon tongue, Sail midsole, and Medium Curry outsole complete this retro design.

The Nike Dunk Low Medium Curry released in March of 2021 and retailed for $100.

name: Diffused Taupe (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Diffused Taupe (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Diffused Taupe (Women's) was released alongside several Dunk Low variations with subdued palettes, including Hemp Sail and Cacao Wow. It pays tribute to iconic Nike basketball shoe silhouettes from the ‘80s while utilizing premium materials.

On this Nike Dunk Low for women the upper is crafted entirely from smooth leather with perforations across the vamp and the Swoosh checked across the side. The use of leather gives the shoe a slightly cushiony appearance that adds a minimal amount of bulk to the silhouette. The Diffused Taupe colorway includes Sail, Plum Eclipse, and Diffused taupe, which presents as an off-white base with taupe accents on the overlays, lace cage, heel tab, and rubber outsole.

Our experts at StockX love the Swoosh detail in Plum Eclipse, which contrasts the light tones found on the rest of the shoe. The women’s size Nike Dunk Low Diffused Taupe (Women's) was released on December 1, 2023, and retailed at $110.

name: Anthracite (2023)
title: Nike Air Foamposite One Anthracite (2023)

name: Supreme Black
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Supreme Black
description:
Supreme and Nike paid homage to an NYC classic with the release of the Nike Air Force 1 Low Supreme Black, now available on StockX. This collaboration adds Supreme’s world-renowned Box Logo to the side of a traditional all-black Air Force 1 design.

This Air Force 1 Low is comprised of an all-black leather upper with matching soles and detailing. A red Supreme Box Logo placed on the outside heel completes the design. These sneakers released in March of 2020 and retailed for $118.

name: Albino & Preto
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Albino & Preto
description:
Step into a blend of cultures with the Nike SB Dunk Low Albino & Preto. The Fossil/Black/Sail colorway is a style statement as well as a reflection of a unique collaboration between the skate and Jiu-Jitsu cultures.

The upper is adorned with heavy gauge canvas, replicating the texture and the grace of Jiu-Jitsu kimonos, while the sail-colored body wrapped in fossil & black accents add a stylish contrast. The black swoosh is a standout feature, epitomizing the duality of Albino & Preto's name and the collaborative essence of this pair. With every step, feel the essence of Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu meeting the skate world. The textile upper features a pearl weave construction traditionally used on jiu-jitsu uniforms, offering not just a visual appeal but a story woven into the fabric of the sneaker. This pair of Dunks are a narrative of tradition meeting modernity. It's about the sail-colored boxes of Nike SB meeting the modern take on Jiu-Jitsu kimonos by Albino & Preto.

Released on September 23, 2023, for a retail price of $130, this pair is not just a purchase but an investment in a legacy of cool. Grab your pair and step into the story.

name: Medium Olive (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Medium Olive (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Medium Olive W dresses the archival hoops shoe in traditional two-tone color blocking.

The all-leather upper of this Dunk Low Medium for women by Nike merges a crisp white base with olive green overlays and a color-matched Swoosh. Underpinning the sneaker is a traditional rubber cupsole, featuring white sidewalls that contain a lightweight foam wedge for cushion. Underfoot, the olive rubber outsole includes the brand´s herringbone traction pattern and rounds of the silhouette.

The Nike Dunk Low Medium Olive W was released the 9th of September 2022 and originally retailed at a price of $110.

name: Drake NOCTA Certified Lover Boy
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low Drake NOCTA Certified Lover Boy
description:
Previously dubbed "Certified Lover Boy", the new premium Drake-inspired AF1 is now known as the "Love You Forever." This sentiment is inspired by Drake’s favorite childhood book with subtle added details of the scripted "Love You Forever" on the midsole, in the same white color. Additional design elements include customized laces, NOCTA logo on left heel, and a new perforation pattern on toe box.
​
The special-edition Drake Nike Air Force 1 Low released December of 2022 for $160.

name: White (Travis Scott Cactus Jack Utopia Edition)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 White (Travis Scott Cactus Jack Utopia Edition)
description:
Unveiled on July 28, 2023, the Nike Air Force 1 Low Travis Scott Cactus Jack Utopia Edition is more than just a sneaker; it's the embodiment of Travis’ creative genius, this shoe echoes with the sounds and themes of his groundbreaking album, 'Utopia’.

Radiating in a dominant all-white shade, this iconic silhouette carries the legacy of the Air Force 1 with a touch of Travis Scott's unique artistry. Crafted with precision, the sneaker showcases the word 'Utopia' imprinted on its heel - a direct nod to Scott's most recent album.

But there's more. The Utopia graphic doesn't just serve aesthetic vibes; it’s a celebration of music and streetwear colliding. The fusion of leather and subtle design details crafts an aesthetic that's both sleek and statement-making. Dive into the Utopia with this pair of sneakers that retailed at $150.

Please note: by listing this item for sale, you agree to ship within the normal shipping window. Shipping deadlines will not be extended to accommodate shipping delays from the retailer.

name: Sportswear Tech Fleece Full-Zip
title: Nike Sportswear Tech Fleece Full-Zip Hoodie Heather Grey/Black
description:
Nike Tech Fleece Full Zip Hoodie is heather grey in color with black accessories.

The Nike Tech Fleece Full Zip Hoodie is made of double-sided spacer fabric. It has long sleeves with black ribbed trimmings. A sleeve pocket on the left arm is fastened with a black zipper. The hoodie also features a full black zipper along the chest to the neck. Front pockets are also reinforced with black studs to prevent damage from pressure from storing objects. There is a small black Nike logo on the left chest.

This Nike Tech Fleece Full Zip Hoodie was released in 2020, retailing at $130.

name: Next Nature Blue Tint (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Blue Tint (Women's)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Blue Tint (Women's) is a low-top sneaker that is part of Nike’s "Next Nature" line. All "Next Nature" shoes are crafted with at least 20 percent recycled material and are part of Nike’s effort to minimize carbon emissions.

This two-toned sneaker for women features a Blue Tint, Cobalt Bliss, Summit White, Volt, and Black colorway that is reminiscent of the sky. The bright Summit White base allows the blue hues on the Swoosh, overlays, lace cage, and outsole to pop. In terms of branding details, the tongue boasts a ‘Nike’ label while ‘NIKE’ is also stitched across the heel.

Something our experts love is the incorporation of the Nike Grind midsole. This speckled midsole is made from recycled shoes from Nike’s Reuse-A-Shoe program and pre-consumer scraps created during manufacturing. The women’s size Nike Dunk Low Next Nature Blue Tint (Women's) was released on September 8, 2023, and retailed at $115.

name: Fog (2021/2023)
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Fog (2021/2023)
description:
The Nike Dunk SB Low Fog is a skateboarding sneaker that slightly resembles the Nike Dunk SB High Fog released in 2005. Designed to provide individuals with the comfort they need while skateboarding, this sneaker features a black suede upper contrasted with a gray leather Nike Swoosh logo on its side and a grey Nike SB branding on its heel. It also features a mesh tongue, black laces, a dark midsole, a black rubber sole, and a gum rubber outsole.

The Nike Dunk SB Low Fog was released in 2021. Originally, it had a retail price of $100.

name: Championship Court Purple
title: Nike Dunk Low Championship Court Purple
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Championship Purple features a white leather upper with Championship Purple overlays and Swooshes. Nike embroidery at the heel pays tribute to the original 1985 design. At the base, a white and purple sole adds the finishing touch.

The Nike Dunk Low Championship Purple releases in May of 2022 and retails for $100.

name: White Black Panda (PS)
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black Panda (PS)
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black PS features an entirely white leather upper with black overlays. The touches of black continue to the Swoosh branding, and the vintage basketball shoe is finished off with a padded collar and nylon mesh tongue, a white midsole, and a black outsole and treading. 

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black PS was released in March 2021 and originally retailed for $65.

name: Sportswear Tech Fleece Full-Zip
title: Nike Sportswear Tech Fleece Full-Zip Hoodie Black
description:
This Nike Tech Fleece Full Zip Hoodie in black delivers a clean look and extra warmth. Featuring a double-sided spacer fabric, this hoodie is built to provide warmth without the weight. The hoodie features a small black Nike logo on its chest and an extra zippable pocket on the left arm.

The black Nike Tech Fleece Full Zip Hoodie was originally made available at the retail price of $130.

name: Grinch (2020)
title: Nike Kobe 6 Protro Grinch (2020)
description:
Nike opened a new chapter at the end of 2020 and refreshed the Kobe 6 design with the Nike Kobe 6 Protro Grinch. The Kobe 6 Grinch originally debuted in 2011 when Kobe Bryant’s Los Angeles Lakers faced LeBron James’ Miami Heat in a legendary match up on Christmas Day. This is the first Kobe 6 to receive the Kobe Protro treatment, a design process that takes classic Kobe designs and updates them with modern tech for improved performance.

At a first glance, the Nike Kobe 6 Grinch looks identically like the OG pair from 2011: it features a Green Apple and Volt textured, snake-inspired upper as a tribute to Kobe’s Black Mamba moniker. A black Swoosh, red Kobe branding on the tongue, and green translucent outsole accentuate the shoe’s reptile theme. But, because this is a Protro, there are some differences. The updated Kobe 6 Grinch arrives with a more responsive Zoom Air cushioning system and scaled-down traction for an improved court feel. The silhouette shape is even altered to provide a lower, sleeker fit.

The Nike Kobe 6 Grinch released in December of 2020 and retailed for $180.

name: Chicago Split
title: Nike Dunk Low Chicago Split
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Chicago Split boasts a fierce colorway combo of University Red, Black, Light Silver, and White. This sneaker dropped on July 14, 2023. Challenging conventional aesthetics, this Dunk Low model remixes a classic silhouette with a split color design, creating a bold contrast that demands attention.

The upper features university red and white on the medial and lateral sides respectively, with light silver and black dressing the Swoosh logo lending the design its 'split' distinction. A clean white midsole offset the strong, contrasting colors, and a black and white outsole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Chicago Split hit the shelves on July 14, 2023, at a retail price of $110.

name: White (Travis Scott Cactus Jack Utopia Edition)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 White (Travis Scott Cactus Jack Utopia Edition)
description:
Unveiled on July 28, 2023, the Nike Air Force 1 Low Travis Scott Cactus Jack Utopia Edition is more than just a sneaker; it's the embodiment of Travis’ creative genius, this shoe echoes with the sounds and themes of his groundbreaking album, 'Utopia’.

Radiating in a dominant all-white shade, this iconic silhouette carries the legacy of the Air Force 1 with a touch of Travis Scott's unique artistry. Crafted with precision, the sneaker showcases the word 'Utopia' imprinted on its heel - a direct nod to Scott's most recent album.

But there's more. The Utopia graphic doesn't just serve aesthetic vibes; it’s a celebration of music and streetwear colliding. The fusion of leather and subtle design details crafts an aesthetic that's both sleek and statement-making. Dive into the Utopia with this pair of sneakers that retailed at $150.

Please note: by listing this item for sale, you agree to ship within the normal shipping window. Shipping deadlines will not be extended to accommodate shipping delays from the retailer.

name: White Pure Platinum
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Pure Platinum
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Pure Platinum is a low-top counterpart to the classic Dunk High silhouette. 

The Nike Dunk Low Retro has an all-leather construction leaving the Swoosh logos, outsole, and branded heel tabs in a Platinum grey tone. The shoe has a low-cut padded collar and a perforated toe box with Nike branding in the woven tongue tag, sock liner, and heel tab. It has a rubber cupsole for traction with stitched sidewall construction and an interior foam wedge for comfort. 

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Pure Platinum was released on 19th November 2022. Upon its launch, its retail price was $110.

name: Hunger
title: Nike Ja 1 Hunger
description:
The Nike Ja 1 Hunger is presented in various color combinations incorporating leather and ballistic mesh on its upper. The mesh covers its vamp and side panel, while leather material is featured on the majority of its upper.​
​
​This sneaker comes in game royal, university red, black, bright crimson, photo blue, and vivid orange color schemes. The mismatched design highlights the right foot's top in the game royal color scheme while emphasizing the left foot with a vivid crimson hue. The features a characteristic "Ja" marking with his number "12" on the heels as well as the hunger logo printed on its tongue in orange, with black letter scribbles on its heel counter completing the overall appearance.​
​​
​What we love about the Ja Hunger sneaker design is the foam midsole with speckles mirroring the mismatched color tones on the outsoles, a black wraparound TPU Swoosh, and the springy Zoom Air Unit on the forefoot, providing cushioning. The Nike Ja 1 Hunger was released on 25th May 2023. The sneaker initially retailed at $110.

name: Triple Pink (PS)
title: Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (PS)
description:
Since its first release, the Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Preschool)remains one of the high-selling variants of the Nike Dunk Low series.
​
The upper of Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Preschool) is constructed with light pink-layered leather featuring darker pink overlays of synthetic leather made from recycled polyester material. The toe box is made of pink perforated leather. Its pull tab, which is embroidered with the symbol of "NIKE," is also constructed using pink synthetic leather. The midsole and outsole of the Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Preschool) are made of pink and white rubber.
​
Nike Dunk Low Triple Pink (Preschool) was first released on September 13, 2022, at a price of $85.

name: Clear Jade
title: Nike Dunk Low Clear Jade
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Clear Jade takes a classic silhouette and dresses it in a two-tone colorway that pops.​
​​
​The Clear Jade Nike Dunk Low-Top features a white leather upper with a perforated toebox for breathability. Clear Jade leather is used for the side panel Nike Swoosh and the overlays surrounding the toebox, eyestays, heel, and collar. The tongue is white with Clear Jade trim, and a white branding patch with Clear Jade Nike branding. The padded sock liner is Clear Jade, and the insole is Clear Jade with white Nike branding. The foam cushion midsole is fully sewn-in and sits atop a rubber cup sole. The outsole is Clear Jade rubber with a traction pattern in concentric circles.​
​
​The detail that our sneaker experts appreciate most about this sports shoe is the white embroidery that makes up the Nike branding on the Clear Jade heel tab. The Nike Dunk Low Clear Jade was released on July 1st, 2023, for a retail price of $110.

name: Drake White Chrome
title: Nike NOCTA Glide Drake White Chrome
description:
The Nike NOCTA Glide Drake White Chrome is an all-white version of the Nike NOCTA Glide, a collaboration between Nike and Canadian rapper Drake. The sneaker finds inspiration in the Nike Zoom Flight 95 but incorporates mesh instead of premium leather on the upper.

Like other iterations of the NOCTA Glide, the "White Chrome" model comes with bubble-like chrome detailing on the bulky, foam midsole and 3M reflective piping. A Zoom Air unit in the forefoot complements the Phylon midsole and adds extra cushioning. The midfoot overlay is made of a breathable woven textile and features a small Swoosh. In addition, NOCTA branding can be found on the padded tongue and debossed on the chrome details on the heel.

Something our experts love is the triple-branded insole, which features logos from Nike, NOCTA, and G-Tek. The Nike NOCTA Glide Drake White Chrome was released on October 27, 2023, and retailed at $160.

name: Supreme Wheat
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low SP Supreme Wheat
description:
Drawing inspiration from classic work boots, the Nike Air Force 1 Low SP Supreme Wheat features a Flax Durabuck upper with Supreme Box Logo insignias on the lateral heels. At the base, a matching Flax Air sole completes the design. This model was exclusively sold through Supreme stores and their online shops.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low SP Supreme Wheat released in November of 2021 and retailed for $150.

name: Halloween Zombie
title: Nike Ja 1 Halloween
description:
Step into the eerie season with the Nike Ja 1 "Halloween" a sneaker that beautifully marries innovative design with a spooky aesthetic. This edition, wrapped in a Lime Blast/Oil Green-Black-Hemp-Cacao Wow colorway, brings a fresh and spooky vibe to the courts. The upper, crafted with synthetic materials and mesh ensures a comfortable and breathable fit. The design is a salute to the Halloween spirit, echoing haunting stories with every stride you take.

The innovative tech in the sneaker doesn't take a backseat to aesthetics. The colorway is more than just a visual treat; it's a representation of Nike's commitment to evolving sneaker culture. The zombie scratches across the iconic Swooshes, the eerie hands rising from graves, and the blood-red embroidered number "12" are a tale of spooky elegance blended with sporty functionality. This is where the tradition of Halloween meets the futuristic design of Nike, creating a sneaker that's as visually appealing as it is performance-ready.

With the Nike Ja 1 "Halloween" you're stepping into a narrative crafted meticulously by Nike and Ja Morant. The eerie yet exciting colorway, coupled with the innovative design, makes it a coveted possession for any sneakerhead. Dropping on October 28, 2023, at a retail price of $120, the Nike Ja 1 "Halloween" is a sweet deal for those ready to make a statement on and off the court.

name: Hyper Pink
title: Nike Zoom GT Cut 2 Hyper Pink
description:
The Nike Zoom GT Cut 2 Hyper Pink is part of the second edition of Nike’s Greater Than (GT) series with a focus on Air Zoom technology. As the name implies, this high-performance basketball shoe is designed for cutting across the court and changing directions quickly.

The sneaker features a Zoom Air unit in the heel and another layered beneath the upper. When combined with the supportive insole, these cushioning units allow for increased responsiveness. A vibrant pink colorway featuring Hyper Pink, Fierce Pink, Pearl Pink, and Gym Red covers the texturized knit upper while a darker Fireberry color makes the heel and tread stand out.

Something our experts love about this basketball shoe is the contrasting Swooshes on the side panel and the midsole. They face in opposite directions and create the appearance of movement, embodying the rapid "cut" motion that inspired the shoe’s name. The Nike Zoom GT Cut 2 Hyper Pink was released on August 10, 2023, and retailed at $170.

name: Mica Green
title: Nike Dunk Low Mica Green
description:
Nike is adding the recently popular Mica Green colorway to part of its Spring/Summer 2023 collection, with the addition of the Nike Dunk Low Mica Green.

The Nike Dunk Low Mica Green is constructed using a Photon Dust canvas and Mica Green leather uppers. Nike used a sail midsole to help give the sneaker a vintage inspired look, and used Mica Green laces to sit over the matching colored tongue.

The Nike Dunk Low Mica Green released May 16, 2023, with a retail price of $110.

name: Red Stardust (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Red Stardust (Women's)

name: Tweed Midnight Navy Corduroy
title: Nike Dunk Low Tweed Midnight Navy Corduroy

name: April Skateboards
title: Nike SB Dunk Low April Skateboards
description:
Strap in for a ride with the Nike SB Dunk Low April Skateboards, a sneaker that’s as much about performance as it is about making a statement. The Turbo Green/Metallic Silver/Turbo Green colorway is a nod to the fearless energy of the skate parks.

The design stays true to the SB Dunk Low's heritage, blending functionality with street-ready aesthetics. This sneaker brings a bold twist to the classic design, incorporating a color pop that stands out against the concrete playgrounds. It's built to withstand the scrapes and scratches of skate life, all while keeping your style on point.

Priced at a cool $120, the April Skateboards edition is an affordable piece of skateboarding's rich culture. Set to drop on November 27, 2023. It's a colorway that represents more than just style. It's a testament to the skate scene's vibrant personality and a must-have for those who live to ride.

name: Travis Scott Cactus Jack
title: Nike Mac Attack QS SP Travis Scott Cactus Jack

name: Light Orewood Brown
title: Nike Dunk Low Premium Light Orewood Brown
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Premium Light Orewood Brown dons the classic Dunk Low low-top silhouette and features a Light Orewood Brown colorway, creating a warm and earthy aesthetic.

The Light Orewood Brown Nike Dunk Low Premium boasts a subtle ivory tone on its upper, which is crafted from breathable canvas and accented with leather overlays at the forefoot and heel. Nike's branding is tastefully incorporated, adorning both the woven tongue tag and the rear tab. The low-top Dunk Low is set atop a cream-colored cup sole, complete with an internal foam wedge for added comfort, and a rubber outsole providing traction and grip.

Our experts say the Nike Dunk Low Premium Light Orewood Brown colorway is the best feature, with a rich and sophisticated appearance. The Light Orewood Brown hue adds a touch of elegance to the classic Dunk Low silhouette, making it a stylish and versatile choice for people who appreciate a classic design with a contemporary twist. The shoe was released on August 30th, 2023, for $120.

name: Next Nature White Light Orewood Brown (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Next Nature White Light Orewood Brown (Women's)
description:
Constructed of FlyLeather, a leather-like material made up of at least 50% recycled materials, the women's Nike Dunk Low Next Nature White Light Orewood Brown (W) features simple color blocking similar to the original 1985 Nike Dunk. It features a white base with Orewood Brown overlays and Swooshes. From there, a white and grey Air sole completes the design.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Next Nature White Light Orewood Brown (W) released in March of 2022 and retailed for $105.

name: Anthracite
title: Nike Dunk Low Anthracite

name: Red Swoosh Panda
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro Red Swoosh Panda
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro Red Swoosh Panda is dressed in a mix of three major colors: white, university red, and black.
​
​The white accents on the tongue tags and leather overlays contrast with the black leather foundation of this Retro Nike Dunk model. Red heels, Swooshes, as well as a rubber outsole with cushioning technology, are visible in the shoe's design. The white lace closure system, lining, black outsole, and white midsole complete the look.
​
​The Nike Dunk Low Retro Red Swoosh Panda made its debut on October 1st, 2022, for a recommended retail price of $110.

name: Vintage Green (Women's)
title: Nike Dunk Low Vintage Green (Women's)
description:
Constructed with a smooth white and Pro Green leather upper, the women's Nike Dunk Low Vintage Green (W) explores the same two-tone color blocking featured on the first line of Nike Dunks in 1985. From there, vintage-styled, yellowed soles and laces add the finishing touches to this retro design.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Vintage Green (W) released in March of 2022 and retailed for $110.

name: Aunt Pearl
title: Nike KD 3 Aunt Pearl
description:
The Nike KD 3 Aunt Pearl is a variation of Kevin Durant’s Nike KD 3 with a pink, pearlescent color scheme first seen in the Nike KD 4 edition. This vibrant colorway pays tribute to Kevin Durant’s aunt who played a significant role in his life and passed away in 2000 from lung cancer.

The KD 3 Aunt Pearl features retro upgrades without retooling the interior of the shoe. It includes ballistic mesh sidewalls that provide support without sacrificing breathability. The upper also boasts smooth leather and flexible synthetic materials, which are covered in soft pink colors. The leather overlays and tongue display a pearly sheen that compliments the translucent tread on the bottom of the shoe.

Something our experts love is the mismatched branding details on the tongues. The right shoe’s tongue features KD branding, while the left shoe’s tongue showcases the Kay Yow Cancer Fund logo. The Nike KD 3 Aunt Pearl was released on October 15, 2023, and retailed at $130.

name: Valentine's Day (2023)
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro PRM Valentine's Day (2023)
description:
Nike is celebrating Valentine’s Day this year with the release of the Nike Dunk Low Retro PRM Valentine’s Day (2023). Nike’s 2023 Valentine’s Day collection consisted of the Dunk Low, Air Trainer 1, Uptempo 96, and Air Force 1 silhouettes.

The Nike Valentine’s Day Dunk Low has a burgundy and sail leather upper with a tumbled pink leather Swoosh. The limited edition sneakers have burgundy outsoles, a mesh sockliner, and is tied off with burgundy shoe laces.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro PRM Valentine’s Day (2023) released February 7, 2023 with a retail price of $120.

name: Sportswear Tech Fleece
title: Nike Sportswear Tech Fleece Full-Zip Hoodie & Joggers Set Black
description:
The Nike Tech Fleece Full Zip Hoodie Joggers Set Black is made of a tri-layer material and is available in a black colorway.

This set includes a classic Tech Fleece hoodie and jogger pants. The tri-layer fabric comprises a brushed inside lining material, a posh foam in the middle and a jersey on the outside. Apart from that, the hoodie is fully zipped and comes with a zipper pocket on the left arm. The jogger pants are branded with Nike’s brand name and a Swoosh below it. Further, the pants feature a drawstring cord for adjustment.

The Nike Tech Fleece Full Zip Hoodie Joggers Set Black debuted on January 15th, 2022 and retailed for $240.

name: Black Total Orange Mini Swoosh
title: Nike Dunk Low Black Total Orange Mini Swoosh
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Black Total Orange Mini Swoosh is a low-top sneaker in the Nike Dunk line.

The Dunk Low Black Total Orange Mini Swoosh features Total Orange accenting against a black and white base. The shoe's upper is constructed from leather, which provides durability and comfort. The toebox includes perforated detailing that improves breathability, allowing air to circulate to keep the feet fresh. The midsole is made of hard foam, providing exceptional comfort, support, and shock absorption. A rubber outsole offers adequate traction and stability, providing support and grip to the wearer.

We believe that the distinctive feature of the Nike Dunk Low Black Total Orange Mini Swoosh is the use of mini-Swoosh logos on the toe and tongue. These miniature Swooshes have a unique placement, making them visible only upon close observation of the shoe. The sneaker was released on July 29th, 2023, at a price of $110.

name: Red Panda
title: Nike Dunk Low Red Panda
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Red Panda takes the Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black, also known as the "Panda Dunk," and applies a new colorway. Instead of monochromatic black and white, the Red Panda comes with Velvet Brown, Sanddrift, and Rugged Orange color blocking.

The dark, shaggy suede upper is contrasted by the Rugged Orange of the suede heel overlays, heel tab, and the ‘NIKE’ branding on the texturized tongue. Additional color blocking includes smooth leather details in Sanddrift, including the Swoosh, the toe box, and the lace cage. On the bottom, the sneaker features a dark midsole and a matching rubber outsole.

Something our experts love about this sneaker is how the shaggy suede upper mimics the texture of panda fur and the texturized pattern on the tongue resembles the traditional black and white panda colors. The Nike Dunk Low Red Panda was released on October 27, 2023, and retailed at $120.

name: Triple Black
title: Nike Air VaporMax Plus Triple Black
description:
The Nike VaporMax Plus Triple Black is a combination of the Air Max Plus series, which was released in 1998, and the VaporMax series.

The Nike VaporMax Plus Triple Black has an upper construction of neoprene, true to the iconic look of the Nike Air Max Plus. The length of the Air Max sole extends through the entire sneaker. The tongue displays the Air Vapor Max Plus branding, and the VM logo is seen on the heel. The VM logo provides contrast through its yellow, white, and red colors. The heel is reminiscent of the Tuned Air Logo from 1998. Short white stripes run through the upper part of the Nike VaporMax complete the design.

The Nike Air VaporMax Plus Triple Black released in January of 2018 and retailed for $190.

name: LeBron James Fruity Pebbles
title: Nike Dunk Low QS LeBron James Fruity Pebbles
description:
The Nike Dunk Low QS LeBron James Fruity Pebbles come in Habanero Red mixed with Laser Blue and White colorway.

This Dunk Low sneaker by Nike features a smooth white leather base contrasted with habanero red overlays and a laser blue dressed side Swoosh. The shoe’s white tongue is decorated with the woven Fruity Pebbles tags, while the heel tab is embroidered with LeBron’s LJ logo. The interior part of the sneaker is a Nike-branded sock liner revealing another Fruity Pebble graphic print. Concluding the design is the treaded milky translucent rubber outsole.

The Nike Dunk Low QS LeBron James Fruity Pebbles was released in November 2022 and retailed at $120.

name: Triple Black (2020/2023)
title: Nike Air Max 2 CB '94 Triple Black (2020/2023)
description:
Nike added a new spin on Charles Barkley's 1994 pro model with the Nike Air Max 2 CB 94 Triple Black 2020. From top to bottom, the Nike Air Max 2 CB 94 Triple Black 2020 features an all-black color scheme. Different textures like wrinkled leather, Air Max soles, and a thread-stitched Nike logo add variety to the monotone palette. To finalize this design, the Triple Black has a streak of dark blue in the Air unit.

The Nike Air Max 2 CB 94 Triple Black 2020 released in October of 2020 and retailed for $160.

name: White Black Panda (TD)
title: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black Panda (TD)
description:
A toddler’s shoe (TD), the Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black TD comes in a classic colorway. Crafted from soft leather, the Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (TD) upper is made from a white base overlaid by contrasting black throughout. The black extends to the iconic Swoosh branding and the lightly padded nylon tongue. The tooling continues the two-toned design to include a white midsole and a black rubber outsole that draws directly from the Air Jordan 1.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (TD) was released in March 2021 at a retail price of $50.

name: Reverse Panda
title: Nike Dunk Low Jumbo Reverse Panda
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Jumbo Reverse Panda arrives following the classic "Panda" style, with the sneaker achieving a harmonious balance of black and white tones across its low-top silhouette.

The Reverse Panda Nike Dunk Low Jumbo textile base layers sport a predominantly black tone, while the textured leather overlays starkly contrast in Crisp White. These overlays extend to elongated panels on the tongue. The mesh base and padded tongue have a Sleek Black finish, while the leather overlays and Swooshes come to life in bright white. Various accents of contrast stitching in white, including on the standard black laces, add subtle detail. Below, the sole unit undergoes modifications, with added reinforcement at the toe and a distinct traction pattern.

What our experts love about the Nike Dunk Low Jumbo Reverse Panda is its distinctive and innovative design. This sneaker takes the iconic "Panda" color blocking theme and flips it on its head, creating a fresh and captivating twist on a classic. The sneaker debuted for $120 on June 20th, 2023.

name: Black
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Black
description:
The all-black Air Force 1 Low is a timeless classic in Nike's catalog of heritage sneakers.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Black features a triple black smooth leather upper with a matching Air sole and laces. Subtle Nike Air embroidery on the heel tab nods to the history of the AF-1 line. A metallic lace tag and woven tongue label complete the design.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 retails for $115.

name: Midnight Navy University Blue
title: Nike Dunk Low Midnight Navy University Blue
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Midnight Navy University Blue comes in a Midnight Navy and white colorway with University Blue and Laser Orange accents.

The upper of the Dunk Low Midnight Navy University Blue is made of durable leather, which provides the shoe with both durability. The sneaker sits atop a white midsole and the outsole of the shoe showcases a retro-inspired circular herringbone pattern, perfect for traction and grip. The shoe also features a padded collar and tongue, which ensures that the shoe is comfortable and snug on the feet.

We think that the key feature of the Nike Dunk Low Midnight Navy University Blue is the perforations on the toe box. The perforations are a design element that serves a functional purpose as well. The holes are strategically placed to allow air to circulate through the shoe, which helps to keep the feet cool and dry during intense physical activity. The shoe was released on July 17th, 2023 at a retail price of $110.

name: Athletic Department Deep Jungle
title: Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department Deep Jungle
description:
The Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department Deep Jungle launched as part of the Nike Athletic Department Pack, which brings old-school styling to fan-favorite Nike models. This sneaker follows the Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department University Blue; however, it includes a different nostalgic colorway inspired by varsity sports.

The "Deep Jungle" colorway includes Sail, Deep Jungle, Coconut Milk, and White, which presents as a white base with dark green details. The smooth leather upper comes in Coconut Milk, which contrasts the Deep Jungle found on the suede Swooshes, inner liner, heel tab, and rubber outsole. The sneaker boasts minimal branding, including ‘NIKE’ stitched across the heel tab and the Nike label on the tongue.

Something our experts love is the off-white color of the midsole, which gives the sneaker a worn-in, vintage appearance. The Nike Dunk Low Athletic Department Deep Jungle was released on October 1, 2023, and retailed at $110.

name: The Powerpuff Girls Blossom (PS)
title: Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Blossom (PS)

name: Albino & Preto
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Albino & Preto
description:
Step into a blend of cultures with the Nike SB Dunk Low Albino & Preto. The Fossil/Black/Sail colorway is a style statement as well as a reflection of a unique collaboration between the skate and Jiu-Jitsu cultures.

The upper is adorned with heavy gauge canvas, replicating the texture and the grace of Jiu-Jitsu kimonos, while the sail-colored body wrapped in fossil & black accents add a stylish contrast. The black swoosh is a standout feature, epitomizing the duality of Albino & Preto's name and the collaborative essence of this pair. With every step, feel the essence of Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu meeting the skate world. The textile upper features a pearl weave construction traditionally used on jiu-jitsu uniforms, offering not just a visual appeal but a story woven into the fabric of the sneaker. This pair of Dunks are a narrative of tradition meeting modernity. It's about the sail-colored boxes of Nike SB meeting the modern take on Jiu-Jitsu kimonos by Albino & Preto.

Released on September 23, 2023, for a retail price of $130, this pair is not just a purchase but an investment in a legacy of cool. Grab your pair and step into the story.

name: Light Orewood Brown Sashiko
title: Nike Dunk Low Light Orewood Brown Sashiko
description:
Nike is reintroducing Japanese Sashiko stitching into the popular Nike Dunk Low model, after it was last seen used on the Air Force One silhouette in 2022.

The Nike Dunk Low Orewood Brown Sashiko is constructed with a Pale Ivory denim upper that features Orewood Brown contrast stitching throughout. Nike used red Sashiko style stitching across the toe box, heel tab and eyelets. Red Nike branding is placed subtly on the tongue and insoles.

The Nike Dunk Low Light Orewood Brown Sashiko released March 9, 2023, with a retail price of $120.

name: Halo
title: Nike Kobe 8 Protro Halo
description:
Unveiled on August 23, 2023, the Nike Kobe 8 Protro Halo signals the epic return of the iconic Kobe line.

Drenched in a pristine all-white colorway, this sneaker stands as an embodiment of purity, legacy, and unparalleled style. A true nod to the rebirth of the legendary Nike Kobe series, this piece is all about legacy and finesse. From its seamless upper construction to the intricate detailing, every aspect echoes Kobe's timeless style and unwavering commitment to the game. An embodiment of both on-court prowess and off-court style, this sneaker is a must-have for any collection.

Mamba mentality isn't just a mindset; it's a lifestyle. And for those looking to embody that spirit, the Nike Kobe 8 Protro Halo was made available at a retail price of $180. Truly, a timeless tribute to basketball royalty.

name: White (Women's)
title: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 White (Women's)
description:
The women's Nike Air Force 1 Low White silhouette (W) continues the tradition of the 1982 Air Force 1. The sneaker features an all-white leather upper with a perforated toe box and Swoosh overlays. A Nike heel embroidery and white sole completes the design.

The women's Nike Air Force 1 Low White 2018 (W) released in January 2018 and retailed for $90.

name: Panda Black White (2021)
title: Nike Dunk High Panda Black White (2021)
description:
The Nike Dunk High Panda Black White 2021 features a smooth white leather upper with perforations on the toe box. Black leather overlays, eyestays and Swooshes match the black laces. Orange hits on the insole add the Total Orange to the vintage White/Black colorway. The rubber outsole is black with a concentric-circles pattern for traction. The midsole is white with visible threading around the shoe. Black Nike branding appears on the white tongue and the heel features a black loop with arcs of white-on-white horizontal threading below it.

  The Nike Dunk High Panda Black White 2021 was released on January 27, 2022 at a retail price of $115.

name: The Powerpuff Girls Bubbles (PS)
title: Nike SB Dunk Low The Powerpuff Girls Bubbles (PS)

name: Why So Sad?
title: Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Why So Sad?
description:
The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Why So Sad features a mixture of colors, with coastal blue and light current blue being the dominant hues.

The upper of this Low Nike SB Dunk is made from leather material and there is a white Fat-style SB lacing system. The lateral heel of this shoe features an embroidered chicken that seems to be riding on a skateboard. Additionally, the heels and the tongues of this sneaker have Nike SB branding.

The Nike SB Dunk Low Pro Why So Sad retailed at a price of $120 at the time of its release on November 4, 2022.
